    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>East Asian vases of a particular shape, being relatively tall with a narrow base, a wide body, and a short neck with narrow opening. Originated as stoneware vessels during the Tang dynasty (618-907) and used for wine; later made of ceramic and used for the display of branches of plum tree blossoms. May be lidded.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
